shared_text:
Oakland Primary School - School Page
September 4 at 10:04 AM ·

Here is a snapshot of our teachers trying to make those important early connections with our students. It is so much harder to teach to a computer screen but they are doing all they can to make it work. These are some incredibly dedicated and loving staff members working hard to educate, feed, and keep students safe in this unusual time. You will see our dedicated cafeteria, and office staff as well as one of our IT guys all working to keep this train moving. Thank You also to CVS who came out to the school today to give flu shots to the staff that needed them it was very much appreciated.

Just remember if the teachers are by themselves in their classroom teaching they do not have to wear a mask... but they are very good about masking up where necessary.
Happy Friday.

Do you want to help Sumter School District receive 4,000 masks? Participate in the Masks for Class Challenge sponsored by Santee-Lynches Regional Council of Government.

On September 2 from 12 AM-11:59 PM,post a picture of yourself wearing a mask on Facebook, Instagram and Twitter. For every photo that is posted, Sumter School District will receive 10 masks. Make sure the post is set to public.

In order to be counted, please make sure your post includes the following: @santeelynches@SumterSCSchools
#MasksForClassChallenge

Christ Community Church has supported Cherryvale Elementary for years now, and they knew they could play a role to help teachers and students prepare for school this fall amid the pandemic. They asked for school supply lists from each teacher at the school and then packed and donated supplies to them. We stopped by to see what kind of supplies they needed and how the delivery went.

City of Sumter, South Carolina
August 16 at 4:46 PM ·

You are invited to join us online this week for the All-America City Awards #aac2020. Your community will share programs and stories on #healthybodies, #heathyminds and #humanehousing.

The presentation is Monday at 2pm and awards ceremony is Wednesday at 7:30pm - and lots of other activities in between! We hope to bring the title of “All-America Community” home.

Help cheer for the #SumterSC community and one local youth, Briasha Brown who has also been nominated for the John Parr Youth Leadership Award!

More details on how to participate on our website - www.sumtersc.gov.

#teamsumter #sumterstrong #handupnothandout #investingincommunity #lovesumter

post_text: Executive Director of Operations Samuel Myers and Willow Drive Elementary Principal Preston Spratt conducted a walkthrough with the Sumter Item to discuss sanitization procedures and changes for the upcoming school year. The safety of our students and staff is our top priority. In an effort to enhance our disinfecting procedures, building services staff will utilize electrostatic sprayers to sanitize our schools and buses. Touchpoints like door handles and desks will be sanitized throughout the day. Additional safety protocols for classrooms, transportation, and school meals are available on our website. By working together, we can help ensure the safety of our students and staff. #SumterStrong

post_text: The South Carolina Department of Education approved Sumter School District’s Reopening of Schools Plan. All students will begin online August 28, and we will reevaluate our transition to in-person instruction every two weeks. Unlike the emergency remote learning that was required during COVID-19 school closures, students participating in virtual options will have a daily instructional schedule, receive frequent teacher feedback, and face high standards for earning passing grades. Information regarding the reopening of schools is available on our website at http://sumterschools.net/reentry-plan/. #SumterStrong

post_text:
The City of Sumter, in partnership with Sumter School District, is facilitating a virtual STEAM Career Camp from July 15 – August 1 at four Sumter area elementary schools. The camp is a result of the City of Sumter receiving federal program funds.

Teachers, community partners and parents will assist in linking employability skills training, high engagement WeDo Lego’s Education STEM Kits and high interest books to prepare students for the workforce. Representatives from the City of Sumter will work in concert with teachers to reinforce soft skills such as adaptability, flexibility, leadership, and problem solving in a virtual classroom setting. Teachers will engage in guiding the instruction of employability skills and the free WeDo 2.0 Curriculum at least one hour per day during the three-week camp. The students will be challenged to use the newly taught skills in a real-life STEM scenario, such as an unprecedented flood in the Sumter community. #TeamSumter #SumterStrong

post_text: TikTok donated $1.25 million to National PTA for Covid-19 relief funds. National PTA is awarding 150 local units $5,000 and Districts $15,000 for this grant. The grant application is due July 12. District 13 PTA is applying for this grant to help our local schools and community. The issue area we chose to work on is mental health/social emotional support. We are looking for YOUR input. Please let us know what you think we can do to help your children or students mental health during this pandemic if we receive these grant funds. District 13 PTA will discuss the responses, and all answers are 100% anonymous. Thank you for your time!

Reopening of Schools Feedback Needed

(Please visit our website at www.sumterschools.net to complete the survey.)

Planning is well underway for the 2020-21 school year. COVID-19 has presented a number of challenges, and our commitment to a safe learning environment for students and employees means school may look much different this fall. A key step in our planning is to seek feedback from our stakeholders. The Sumter School District Reopening Schools Task Force is conducting a survey of students, parents, and employees in an attempt to understand how our stakeholders feel regarding the possibilities of our return to teaching and learning in the fall.

Thank you for working with us to help ensure a safe environment for all. #SumterStrong

Bates Middle School
June 7 at 3:26 PM ·

The South Carolina Department of Education (SCDE) has crafted a framework that focuses on teacher and administrative (collective)leadership to drive student mastery of all elements in the Profile of the South Carolina Graduate.

Bates Middle School has been selected to participate in the third statewide cohort of the Collective Leadership Institute.

One of the core principles of Bates Middle School is a focus on teacher leadership, so this is a natural next step in the school's journey to taking its STEM's program to the next level.

post_text: Celebrating our seniors! Congratulations once again to the Hailey Bordeaux Scholarship for Future Educators recipients! #SumterStrong
shared_text:
The Sumter Item
May 28 at 8:10 PM ·

The Sumter Teacher Forum is an annually evolving group of the Sumter School District’s previous year’s and current teachers of the year, and they get together throughout the year for professional development and other initiatives. One of their big projects in recent years has become the Hailey Bordeaux Memorial Scholarship, set up to honor a Sumter native who tragically lost her life before fulfilling her dream to become a teacher. With social distancing in mind, the Sumter Teacher Forum recently surprised the scholarship winners at the district office.

Presented by University of South Carolina Sumter Sumter Opera House & Air Solutions Heating and Cooling

shared_text:
The Sumter Item
May 22 at 12:07 PM ·

Sumter School District administration surprised three district teacher of the year finalists on Friday afternoon with personal messages on their recognition, and two were delivered right to their doorstep. With schools being closed since mid-March because of the pandemic, Superintendent Penelope Martin-Knox and her staff had to get creative. They came up with the idea of the personal home visits outside in the front yard. The district plans to name its district teacher of the year in August, just before the beginning of the new school year.

Presented by University of South Carolina SumterSumter Opera House & Air Solutions Heating and Cooling

shared_text:
Crestwood FFA Chapter
May 18 at 3:23 PM ·

Amazing news was received today. First, the Crestwood FFA chapter was named a Gold chapter by the SCFFA Association, meaning the chapter is one of the top chapters in South Carolina for the 2019-2020 school year. This is the second year in a row the chapter has received this honor, and the fourth time overall. Second, eight students earned their state degrees, which is the highest degree a student may receive by the state association. Those students are Kiera Brown, Caleb Buford, Nathan Clement, Ma’niya Dawson, Raven Dorio-Howard, Sydney Maynard, Kaylan Sanders, and Guillermo Vargas. Congratulations to the chapter and these amazing students! 💙💛 #Impact #SumterStrong

post_text:
Congratulations to Kris Horne from Lakewood High School for being named a Harmon Scholar. He will receive $26,000 to go toward tuition at Clemson University, $1,500 for a laptop and accessories, and $750 per semester for expenses.

This renewable scholarship was established to help students realize the American Dream. Applicants must be a graduating senior from a public high school in Sumter County, South Carolina with a minimum 3.0 GPA on a 4.0 scale. Applicants must attend either Clemson University or University of South Carolina (Columbia) as a full-time student and pursue a degree in accounting, business administration, computer science, education (teaching), engineering, math or other traditional sciences. #SumterStrong
